snippet.textDisplay: maybe it's just because our experiences are different, but I've lived in New York City off and on my entire life and I've never paid any of those weird, crazy, fees. The good faith deposit for example is super illegal and usually a scam. People coming here thinking that's normal are primed for heartbreak. It's usually just first month's rent and security deposit. then there's like small little details about your video, like it's not "East/West Village" it's "The East/West village".Also most apartments I've been in,  mine and my friends included all have full size bathtubs, it's definitely not rare. Additionally your current bathroom situation might be breaking some city codes. reading through theses comments it seems like you're giving an impression of what it's like to live in a city (describing neighborhoods and their culture incorrectly for example) you don't know that much about yet. which is fine! but maybe wait a bit before you make an informational video about moving here. hope that didn't come across too critical cuz I really didn't want it to. enjoy the city!

First of all, renting is almost always done over the internet here in Sweden, you upload your monthly income and contact to the landlord you're currently having. When I studied my boyfriend and I rented a two bedroom apartment 10 min from the city for $900 in a beautiful neighborhood close to the water
